Solent Breezes is ideal for lazy days in the sun, but should you prefer, the more energetic can enjoy a game of tennis, followed by a refreshing dip in our heated outdoor pool. For entertainment we have regular cabarets and live bands performing twice a week, with a livelier programme during the summer tour season.

There's also lots to see and do in the local area including the Norman town of Winchester, and popular attraction of Port Solent, both only a scenic drive away.

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: A popular park close to the beach with something for everyone.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
St Osyth Beach Holiday park near Clacton-on-Sea - a breath of fresh, salty air on the Essex coast.

As its name suggests St Osyth Beach enjoys an amazing beach front location. Guest can pack a beach bag, and simply stroll from the park for direct access to miles of beautiful sandy beaches.

With an excellent range of facilities including a heated indoor swimming pool, a freshwater fishing lake, an attractive entertainment venue, and Kid's Club, this is the ideal choice for people holidaying in Essex. Holiday guests at St Osyth Beach are also welcome to use the many facilities at the neighbouring parks of Martello Beach and Seawick.

The nearby resort of Clacton-on-Sea is very fashionable, as more people decide to take their holidays in England, and flock to the traditional seaside resorts. Clacton's entertainment centres around its famous pier but there are also 2 theatres and a huge programme of entertainment throughout the summer, including the legendary Air Show.

Other Essex attraction highlights include Colchester Zoo, Colchester Castle Museum, and the East Anglian Railway Museum, or if you are up for a drive, Adventure Island at Southend-on-Sea or Promenade Park in Maldon, all sure to result in unique, everlasting memories.

So why not relax and soak up the rays at St Osyth Beach this holiday season?

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: A lively park with great facilities, a brilliant entertainment venue and pool.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
Seawick Holiday Park is the perfect location for fun-filled family holidays near Clacton.

Our entertainment complex (built just a few years ago) can accommodate up to400 holiday guests, and features astate of the art sound system and stage for our cabaret shows and other lively acts.

There's also the reception area, mini-supermarket and funarcade area to enjoy during your stay.Our restaurant is a fantastic place for tasty food, with a great view of the stage.

Outside, a patio area hosts barbecues, super-size TV screens, seating and tables, and access to Seawick's heated outdoor swimming pool. On park we also have an adventure playground, a football pitch and a Crazy Golf course. You can enjoy even more facilities, including an indoor pool complex, at our sister parks Martello Beach and St Osyth just over the road.

The famous seaside resort of Clacton-on-Sea is nearby where you can enjoy all the fun of the fair on the pier; traditional donkey rides, ten pin bowling, the Seaquarium, and much more. For a more cultured day out chose Colchester Castle Museum or the East Anglian Rail Museum. Or head to the wonderful Colchester Zoo with its many exotic animals and birds.

With a great mix of facilities, entertainment for all ages and lots to see and do in the surrounding area, Seawick is the place to be this holiday season!

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: Miles of sandy beaches nearby, so dont forget to pack your sun lotion.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
Located between the historic towns of Rye and Hastings, Winchelsea Sands is the perfect base to embrace the region's history and its many attractions.

Not that you need to leave the park as we have everything you could wish for right here, including a fantastic entertainment venue (busiest at weekends and during the summer season), and a beautiful outdoor swimming pool.

If you do leave the park and go exploring you will be spoiled for choice. There are lovely beaches located nearby (the stunningly sandy Camber Sands is particularly popular), perfect for those who enjoy soaking up the rays, building sand castles or long leisurely walks by the sea.

Or you can explore the nearby nature reserve with its amazing views and wonderful range of English wildlife, particularly its stunning variety of birds.

Culture vultures will love the nearby town of Rye with its castle, art galleries and quirky selection of fun shops. A bit further away visit the Hop Farm for a great family day out with soft play, rides, farmyard animals, and even a driving school for children - beep beep!

Whether you prefer to stay on the park and take advantage of the great entertainment or would rather explore the magnificent 1066 country, a visit to Winchelsea Sands is highly recommended.

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: Amazing Devon sea views on the English Riviera coast in Paignton.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
On the cusp of the Paignton area lies Waterside Holiday Park, with its spectacular views of the South Devon coastline and the ocean.

From its elevated position, you will enjoy stunning picture postcard views of the Torbay coastline, and it is close to the fabulous beaches and attractions of the famed English Riviera. Stay at Waterside and you can take a trip to beautiful Goodrington Sands, an award winning Blue Flag beach ideal for swimming and topping up the tan.

There's so many good reasons to spend a holiday or short break at Waterside. Relax in our friendly clubhouse and enjoy a tasty bite to eat. During the day you can also recline on the Sun Terrace, with a drink in hand, while the kids have a splashingly good time in the heated outdoor pool.

Waterside is renowned for its amazing setting, along with the famous Steam Railway that borders the park. With easy access out onto the headland, guests can walk through the tunnel under the Steam Railway to remarkable views of the Torquay coastline and coastal paths great for dog walkers and hiking. It's all here in this ideal Devon location.

The wonderful sights come courtesy of the hillside location so it's not particularly suitable for anyone who struggles with slopes, but don't worry, if you prefer your park to be on a flat surface we can thoroughly recommend our sister park, nearby Dawlish Sands.

Our holiday accommodation is based on the flattest part of the holiday park, with parking in most areas just a short walk away.

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: Set in 10 acres of well-maintained grounds and surrounded by rural countryside.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
Located less than 5 miles away from the largest town in North Devon, Barnstaple, Tarka Holiday Park is ideally situated for a relaxing, laid-back visit.

Tarka has no clubhouse, swimming pool or restaurant, but what it does have is a unique atmosphere of serenity and seclusion, perfect for discerning holiday guests where peace and tranquility is pretty high on the holiday wish list. Nestled in its beautiful natural setting, Tarka is the perfect antidote to the everyday stresses of modern life.

Tarka Holiday Park puts you in reach of the many activities and stunning locations North Devon is renowned for; from the golden beaches of Saunton, Croyde, Putsborough, Woolacombe and Instow, to the 180 miles of coastal paths, riversides and magnificent views.

Why not walk or cycle the famous Tarka Trail during your visit? Inspired by Henry Williamsons famous fictional novel, it follows the route taken by "Tarka the Otter" in the book of the same name. The Trail takes you through wonderful Devon scenery, with rich green countryside, wooded river valleys, craggy moorland, and dramatic coastline.

As mentioned Barnstaple is also on our doorstep, and you could spend an entire day visiting the shops, cafs and other attractions; the Pannier Market and the Museum of Barnstaple and North Devon are particular favourites for holiday guests.

So if stunning scenery is your interest youll be spoilt for choice, from the dramatic Jurassic coastline to the north or the open moorland of Exmoor to the east, all no more than a half hour drive away.

Book your North Devon break today!

holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_short_overview: Mersea Island, a perfect combination of rich scenery and wonderful coastline.
holiday_product_overviews.holiday_product_long_overview:
Located on the beautiful West Mersea Beach and within easy reach of the town centre, this Essex park offers a strong mix of relaxation, holiday atmosphere, and remarkable coastline views*.

A small and quiet place to relax, the park is close to the Blackwater Estuary, a large section of which is a triple SSSI (Site of Special Scientific Interest). The inspiring sights will thrill nature lovers, featuring flocks of migrating seabirds, along with a host of wonderful wildlife and flora.

Mersea Island is rightly celebrated for its water sports; Boat lovers and Sailing fanatics, Windsurfers and Kitesurfers will be in their element here. Fishing is also a famous tradition of the Island, a wide variety of tasty fish are regularly caught (sole, skate, bass, mullet, herring and cod) and sold in the specialist restaurants nearby. The area is also revered for its magnificent native Oysters, a delicacy that every touring guest should try!

The surrounding Essex countryside is lots of fun to explore. Why not visit historic Colchester with its many landmarks and world-famous zoo? Or walk the promenade at Clacton-on-Sea, a traditional and authentic seaside hot spot? Essex is also renowned for glorious sunny weather its not called The Sunshine Coast for nothing!

Touring pitches are situated adjacent to our famous beach cabins and sandy beach, available on all-weather hard standing with electric, water and free showers**.

Spend your evenings in our brand new and restaurant and bar The Sandbank, with visiting cabaret acts and appetizing food and drink. West Mersea Holiday Park also benefits from a shop and laundrette.

We also have charming, coloured beach huts along the seafront, a wonderful backdrop to this incredible holiday park.

*Please note: The island can be cut off twice a day by tides. Crossing depends on the high tide levels and times can vary quite considerably. On very high tides this can isolate the island for up to 2 hours.

**The touring field at West Mersea Holiday Park has no immediate facilities. The nearest toilets and services are approximately a 5-10 minute walk away.

For keen golfers, the famous Turnberry course is close by, and dozens of other top courses are just a stones throw away.

With both static caravan holidays and holiday homes for sale, this peaceful park is at once an inviting getaway and a stepping stone to numerous local attractions and attracts consistently positive TripAdvisor reviews.
